    <h2 class="section-title">Local Roots, Global Strength</h2>
    <p>Amora Vida and Surpora Lda. are backed by overseas Chinese entrepreneurs who have lived in Portugal for nearly three decades. As naturalised citizens, they reinvest in the communities where they operate.</p>
    <p>The platform collaborates with Chinese developers that have delivered more than 1,000,000 m² of integrated projects across Asia, contributing institutional discipline and capital depth.</p>
    <p>Local partnerships span Portuguese entrepreneurs in gastronomy, real estate, fashion, food supply, and stone industries, providing supply-chain reach and craftsmanship rooted in the region.</p>
    <p>This blend of local leadership, global development capability, and diversified capital underpins the execution of Quinta do Paço do Infante.</p>
  </div>
</section>

